metadata.name: fx_dungeon_2 #49
metadata.description:
Welcome to fx_dungeon_2, a little roguelike experiment living on the Tezos blockchain. Will you be able to get out of it alive? Each token features a randomly generated dungeon with limited resources. The layout is the same every time (on the same token), but you'll need to master each level perfectly if you want to beat the game - it's very difficult! And if you die, you need to start over ;) To beat the game, you need to go up in the dungeon until you find the final upward stairs!

A warning: this thing is not optimized for mobile phones. You'll need computer to play it! Additionally, while I did my best to bugfix and playtest with friends and helpful members of the community, there might still be bugs that I will be able to fix only in future iterations of the game.

## Controls
[W,A,S,D] or [↑ ↓ → ←] to move
[SPACE] or [E] to interact with stairs you are on or doors you are facing
[I] to bring up / exit the character screen
[P] to toggle sound
[R] to restart the game

## Characters
- The game features different character classes, with different strength, resistance and hunger stats
- The stronger a character is, the more damage it will do to creatures around the dungeon
- The more resistant a character is, the less damage it will receive from enemies and structures

### Warriors
- Warriors have average strength and defense stats. They have an average attack speed

### Berserkers
- Berserks are less strong but more resistant than warriors. They are slow to attack

### Assassins
- Assassins are very strong, but are not very resistant and they take damage very easily. They have a superior attack speed

## Exploration
- There are different floors to explore, from 2 (very common) up to 7 (very rare)
- On each floor you'll find obstacles to break, potions and enemies to fight
- Will you manage your resources correctly? If you die, you'll need to restart the game!
- The map will reveal itself as you explore it

## Potions

## Combat
- To attack an enemy, you must need to be in a tile next to it
- To attack an enemy, just press the key to move towards it
- Combat happens in real time. Smash that keyboard!

### Enemies
- There are different types of enemies, some are weaker and some are stronger
- Rats are very fast, but also very weak and easily killed. They are the most common in the dungeon
- Skeletons are slow, but they do more damage than a rat. They are also less common
- Imps are fast and strong enemies with high defense stats. If you spot one, prepare to smash that keyboard to kill it! They are a rare type of enemy
- There's no UI indications of the current enemy status, approach new fights carefully! You'll know when an enemy is dead when, well, it's dead
- Enemies might look the same, but some are stronger and some are weaker than others, while maintaining their general feel

## Console conditions
- You just got this game out of a yard sale, you can't expect it to be in perfect conditions, but it can happen!
- Despite the conditions of the game console, rest assured that the game will run with no bugs (unless myself, poor coder as I am, messed up with some bits of the code)!

metadata.name: Pride Month Tribute #18
metadata.description:
Sentimentio’s genesis NFT collection centers around celebration.

Capped at just 31 editions, it’s a fusion of coding and data to generate artworks that reflect societal sentiments 
towards the LGBTQ+ community and Pride Month over a three-year period.

Data collected from 100K online articles are transformed into artistic traits that express emotions and sentiments through shapes, color, and movement.
 
Sentiment score, ranging from -1 to +1, indicates whether the overall sentiment of articles is positive, negative, or neutral. Represented visually in the background, shades of white signify positive sentiment scores (0 to 1) whereas backgrounds with dark tones reflect negative sentiment scores (-1 to 0).

Emotions are key to our generative artworks.

The hue of the dots in the Pride Month Tribute NFT collection represents the following emotions.

-happiness: pink, yellow
-anger: red
-sadness: purple
-fear: blue
-surprise: green
-disgust: olive

Feelings can be more intense than others in the different time periods covered by our data. The more powerful a particular emotion, the more prominent that color will be in the artwork.

Other aspects such as the size of the dots or their movements are defined by the beautiful randomness of the code.

#CodingIsArt #sentimentio

metadata.name: The Love Gun #81
metadata.description:
The Love Gun:

Modern day Cupid’s weapon, filled with deadly love. One shot = one lover, hopelessly swooned off their feet. You can’t run, you can’t hide. Cupid’s shot will pierce your heart.

M16 Carbine assault rifle filled with love and art. The physical gun was made with love for NFT_Goat’s IRL Valentine’s Day event on Feb 14, 2023, and sold at an online auction with 100% proceeds going to Kids Upfront charity (https://kidsupfronttoronto.com/).

metadata.name: Mr. Whiskers’ Generative Synthwave Odyssey #5
metadata.description:
A soundscape of synthwave music built using JS. Generates a looped sequence of notes played by a polyphonic synthesizer, with a random selection of scales and beats per minute. Features Mr.Whiskers on synth on a white canvas and one other color chosen from a palette of seven colors. The colors in the palette are variations of black or blue. 

The code defines several pitch sets, including major and minor scales, pentatonic scales, and whole-half diminished scales, and randomly selects one of these sets to use as the basis for the loop (total of 19 scales). The loop is generated using a 16-step grid, with each step representing an eighth note. At each step, the code randomly enables or disables cells in the grid, and if a cell is enabled, the code plays a note on the synthesizer corresponding to the pitch of that cell. The code also randomly changes the beats per minute (bpm) within a range of 120-180 bpm. This creates a sense of variation in the tempo, and combined with the randomization of the scale, can lead to an infinite number of variations. Regardless of its starting point, your distinctive version will maintain a consistent pitch set and bpm throughout.

_____________________________________________

To interact with the artwork:
- Start the music by either pressing the 'm' key or clicking anywhere on the canvas.
- No sight of Mr. Whiskers? No need to worry! Just hit the "c" key to bring him forth!
- To make Mr. Whiskers disappear, simply press the "x" key 
- Hit the "d" key to either open or close the portal
- To pause and restart the music, press the "z" key.
- To save a snapshot of the current image, press "p" and it will be saved as a PNG file. 
- For an SVG file of the original image, press "s".
- There is a possibility of encountering problems with the rendering on certain mobile devices.
_____________________________________________

retr0metr0, San Francisco, May 2023.
CC BY-NC-ND 4.0.

metadata.name: Summer Vibes #8
metadata.description:
This collection was created using p5.js coding to create the artwork. The artwork is layered into its current form through p5.js coding in order to create the artwork shown available here.

The color palette was selected to reflect the vibrations of summer. Summer is a beautiful time of year, with activities in the daytime and the night. The figures that appear in the artwork were created by using the p5.js code to manipulate nested triangles. 

The goal of the line work was produced with p5.js and was created to reflect the warmth, dynamic activity, and quiet moments found during the long days and short nights of summer.

objkt.name: Now There's None of You Left #87

metadata.name: Now There's None of You Left #87
metadata.description:
Strands of memory are twisted and entangled with each other, blending in and out with the surrounding fog of chaos. Each strand, like a thread of a tapestry, weaves a narrative of the self that is inseparable from the whole. Walking through a thick confusion, you see a solitary slice of the self in each iteration. 

Created in Cables.gl, "Now There’s None of You Left" is made from layers of randomly generated transparent shapes and various noise textures that are then distorted with a combination of Perlin and Simplex noise. The distortion is also built up in multiple layers, making the shapes sometimes overlay or coil over each other. All these layers of shapes, textures, noises, and distortions create a complex composition that illustrates distorted memories and eroded mind. The resulting scene can look tranquil, sometimes violent, sometimes almost empty. Strands of memory, tendrils of emotions, all brewing in the broth of forgetfulness. And in the midst of this dense confusion, you pray to find a glimpse of clarity. Are you still you, or are you me?

Controls:

[1] Set resolution to 716 x 1024 (default)

[2] Set resolution to 1433 x 2048

[3] Set resolution to 2688 x 3840

* The presets above are suitable for screen viewing up to 4k screen resolution. To set a custom resolution for printing and other purpose, add &res=[desired resolution] at the end of the URL. It will set the height of the image, and the width will be calculated automatically at 0.7 ratio. For example, to get a resolution of 4911 x 7016px (about the size of A2 paper), add &res=7016 as URL parameter.

[c] Capture a screenshot at rendered resolution in live view

Note:
There might be a very slight difference in the minor details between live view and the preview image rendered by fxhash engine. This discrepancy won't appear when you capture a screenshot using the built-in keyboard shortcut.

metadata.name: Sansuhwa #36
metadata.description: Once upon a time, in a house in an oriental village, you can see beautiful nature when you look at the window. This painting of nature is called "Sansuhwa." You can see the sun or the moon, the mountains, the sea, and the forest, but sometimes you can only see a part of them. And what you see in the bottom right is the way that Asian painting usually signs paintings. Usually, it is written in Chinese characters, but I made it specially in Korean.

metadata.name: Schola #73
metadata.description:
During my school years, I developed an almost meditative habit of drawing circles, over and over, on the pages of my notebooks, until a sea of black rounds formed on each sheet. My involuntary choice always fell on a black pen, colors remained foreign to this practice, except on a few rare occasions...

Press "s" to save a png

metadata.name: Hidden Intersections #73
metadata.description:
In this piece, two grids overlap:

1. a perfect one composed of lines drawn on the screen
2. an irregular one composed of linear zones that reference other parts of the screen

Everything you see in the final composition is a result of the overlapping intersections of these two grids with each other, and eventually themselves.


------------

Created as part of #genuaryTogether for #genuary2023, for the 4th day, theme: "intersections".

source code: https://github.com/protozoo/genuary23_04_intersections

controls:
- "s" key: save a png of the display
- "w" key: generate and save a 4k widescreen version of your seed (it will look different, but always be the same)
